{"questionId":"22770","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is given on the following set of axes. The graph passes through the&nbsp;points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, and has a horizontal asymptote at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/ee338f613e2e47b443364c8f208b72ef959fa927.png\"></p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>On the same set of axes draw the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, showing any intercepts and&nbsp;asymptotes.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/9a44a5af544d4c13f7a9cdd6c75f84e853219469.png\"></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-asymptote&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>concave up decreasing curve and passing through <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22770","referenceCode":"21N.1.AHL.TZ0.10b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-a